React re-renders child when parent re-renders by default. Common causes:

**1. New object/array/function refs each render**
```jsx
// Bad — new ref every render
<Child options={{ foo: true }} />
<Child onClick={() => doThing()} />

// Fix
const options = useMemo(() => ({ foo: true }), []);
const onClick = useCallback(() => doThing(), []);
```

**2. Component not memoized**
```jsx
// Fix — skip re-render if props unchanged
const Child = React.memo(({ value }) => <div>{value}</div>);
```

**3. Context changes**
If child reads context, any context value change re-renders it. Split contexts or memoize the value.

**4. State lifted too high**
State that only child needs sitting in parent — every parent state change triggers child. Move state down.

**Quick diagnosis:**
```jsx
// Add to child to see what changed
import { useEffect, useRef } from 'react';
function useWhyRerender(name, props) {
  const prev = useRef(props);
  useEffect(() => {
    const changed = Object.entries(props).filter(([k,v]) => prev.current[k] !== v);
    console.log(name, 'changed:', changed);
    prev.current = props;
  });
}
```

Or install `why-did-you-render` lib for automatic tracking.

**Fix order:** `React.memo` → `useCallback`/`useMemo` → move state down → split context.

**CORS = browser blocking cross-origin requests.** Happens when your frontend (e.g. `localhost:3000`) hits an API on a different origin (e.g. `api.example.com`).

**Common causes:**

| Cause | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Server missing `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header | Add it server-side |
| Preflight `OPTIONS` request not handled | Add OPTIONS route returning 204 |
| Credentials sent without `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true` | Add header + set `withCredentials` on client |
| Wildcard `*` with credentials | Can't combine — use explicit origin |
| Wrong header in `Access-Control-Allow-Headers` | Add your custom headers to the allowlist |

**Quick server fixes:**

```js
// Express
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Origin', 'https://yourfrontend.com');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Methods', 'GET,POST,PUT,DELETE,OPTIONS');
  res.header('Access-Control-Allow-Headers', 'Content-Type, Authorization');
  if (req.method === 'OPTIONS') return res.sendStatus(204);
  next();
});
```

```python
# FastAPI
from fastapi.middleware.cors import CORSMiddleware
app.add_middleware(CORSMiddleware, allow_origins=["https://yourfrontend.com"], allow_methods=["*"], allow_headers=["*"])
```

**Dev shortcut:** proxy requests through your dev server (Vite: `server.proxy`, Next.js: `rewrites`) so browser sees same origin — no CORS needed.

**Never** set `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` in production with auth — use explicit origins.

