**Event listener accumulation**
```js
// Bad — adds new listener every request
emitter.on('data', handler);

// Fix
emitter.once('data', handler);         // or
emitter.removeListener('data', handler); // when done
```

**Closures holding references**
```js
// Bad — callback keeps entire `req` alive
req.on('end', () => console.log(req.body));

// Fix — extract only what you need
const body = req.body;
